<TEXT>
<P>
OK, you finally got me to write. After 30 years of subscribing to The Times, I 
finally protest and am sending back to you the "Tales of the Crypt" cover of 
our TV guide for the week of June 3. 
</P>
<P>
The cover was disgusting and not a sight I wanted to see every time I picked up 
the guide. 
</P>
<P>
In the future, please be more aware of how this affects small children (my 
grandchildren, to be specific) and at least not be as graphic. 
</P>
<P>
I still love The Times and will forgive this one mistake, but I just felt you 
should know how one subscriber felt about this sort of cover. 
</P>
<P>
Patricia A. Akers, Stanton 
</P>
</TEXT>
