<HEADLINE>
<P>
OUTTAKES: MORE THAN MUSCLE? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Pat H. Broeske 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
While Stallone attempts to branch out, Arnold Schwarzenegger is getting ready 
to go back into action in "Terminator 2: Judgment Day," expected to begin 
rolling in early October in and around L.A. 
</P>
<P>
James Cameron -- who made his directorial debut with the original "Terminator" 
(1984) -- produces, directs and co-writes with William Wisher. (A longtime 
friend and former college roommate of Cameron's, Wisher worked as a consultant 
on the original "Terminator" -- and wrote the film's novelization.) 
</P>
<P>
This time out, the story involves John Connor, the young and troubled son (he's 
already got a police record) of "Terminator's" tough heroine, Sarah Connor, 
again played by Linda Hamilton. Michael Biehn -- the futuristic soldier of "I" 
-- will also be back. 
</P>
<P>
