<HEADLINE>
<P>
RECORD RACK: *** CHRIS THOMAS, "CRY OF THE PROPHETS," SIRE/HIGHTONE: ALBUMS ARE 
RATED ON A SCALE OF ONE STAR (POOR) TO FIVE (A CLASSIC). 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DON WALLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On his major-label debut, the son of minor-league blues man Tabby Thomas 
concocts a strange brew of deep soul, country blues, modern funk, Hendrix and 
Marley that falls somewhere between a more rockin' Robert Cray and a Lenny 
Kravitz without the Lennonisms. Despite a pro forma approach to songwriting and 
a somewhat limited vocal palette, young Thomas gets by on the depth of his 
emotional expression and a stinging, rootsy guitar style. An audience for this 
amalgam awaits. DON WALLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
