<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 MEN DIE FROM GUNSHOT WOUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two San Diego men died of gunshot wounds in separate incidents over the 
weekend, and police said they had no suspects in either case. 
</P>
<P>
In the first incident, Ignacio Orozco, 20, who had moved recently from 
Washington state to the 1600 block of 40th Street, died at 10:10 p.m. Friday at 
Paradise Valley Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses had taken him there after he was shot in the chest and shoulder 
during an argument with another man about 9:40 p.m., San Diego police said. The 
shooting occurred near 40th and Delta streets. 
</P>
<P>
In the second shooting, police said a 27-year-old San Diego man died at Mercy 
Hospital within an hour of being shot early Saturday as he walked near 26th 
Street and Broadway. 
</P>
<P>
Residents said Ruben Zenteno, who lived in the 1600 block of Fern Street, was 
seen walking with a companion at 6 a.m. and that a few minutes later several 
gunshots rang out. 
</P>
<P>
Police responded at 6:14 a.m. and found Zenteno shot in the chest and arm. He 
died at Mercy at 7:02 a.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
