<HEADLINE>
<P>
DANNEMEYER'S ATTACK ON MANDELA TERMED SHAMEFUL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The article "Mandela Talk Draws Cheers From Congress" (June 27) by Times staff 
writer Edwin Chen was indeed inspiring. 
</P>
<P>
It is too bad that Republican Congressman William E. Dannemeyer from Fullerton 
had to show his narrow-minded attitude when he likened Mr. Mandela to H. Rap 
Brown and Willie Horton. Perhaps Rep. Dannemeyer has been too long in office 
and needs a long, worthwhile rest. 
</P>
<P>
JAIME B. VEGA 
</P>
<P>
Santa Ana 
</P>
