</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
David M. Gordon should glance farther east in Europe than Britain for examples 
of what "more equitable" truly means in regard to health care or any other good 
or service. More equitable really means burdening taxation, fewer choices and 
lower quality. 
</P>
<P>
I'm amazed that while many countries are throwing off the chains of state-run 
governments, an American economist calls for the world's leading example of 
economic and political liberty to follow a path to socialism. 
</P>
<P>
RICHARD NONN 
</P>
