<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHERE TO START THE QUEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By F. LISA BEEBE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
How to get there: Iberia Airlines, Aviaco and Air Europa fly to the Balearic 
Islands from Madrid or Barcelona, which is only 30 minutes away. Flights and 
hotels are often hard to come by in the peak months of July and August, so book 
in advance. 
</P>
<P>
In May, June, and September, the weather is still fine and there are fewer 
crowds. 
</P>
<P>
Accommodations: For reservations at Ibiza's Hotel Hacienda, contact Marketing 
Ahead, 433 Fifth Ave., New York 10016, (212) 686-9213. 
</P>
<P>
For reservations at other hotels: 
</P>
<P>
Hotel Formentor, Formentor Peninsula, Puerto de Pollensa, Majorca 07470. 
</P>
<P>
Hotel La Residencia, Deya, Majorca. 
</P>
<P>
Hotel Illa D'Or, 265 Paseo Colon, Puerto de Pollensa, Majorca. 
</P>
<P>
For more information: Contact the National Tourist Office of Spain, 8383 
Wilshire Blvd., Suite 960, Beverly Hills 90211, (213) 658-7188. F. LISA BEEBE 
</P>
</TEXT>
