<HEADLINE>
<P>
6 LONGTIME SOUTH GATE TEACHERS GIVEN HONORS AT RETIREMENT PARTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SOUTH GATE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Six teachers with nearly 150 years of combined teaching experience retired 
recently from South Gate High School. 
</P>
<P>
Physical education teacher Don Guynn had the most years in the profession. He 
retired after 38 years. During his tenure, Guynn also coached football and 
basketball. 
</P>
<P>
Art teacher William Mendoza taught 32 1/2 years. Math teacher Doris Fetters 
taught 26 years, and Madelene Muensterman worked for 22 years. A business 
education teacher, Muensterman was the school's testing coordinator when she 
retired. 
</P>
<P>
Social studies teacher Ruth Russell taught for 17 years, while Reserve 
Officers' Training Corps Sgt. Curtis McKee retired after 14 years. 
</P>
<P>
All of them were honored at a recent retirement party given by their 
colleagues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
