<HEADLINE>
<P>
WINNERS CHOSEN IN CLEANUP WEEK POSTER CONTEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MAYWOOD 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Deanna Fasthorse of Zion Lutheran School won first prize in a cleanup poster 
contest sponsored by the Maywood Chamber of Commerce as part of the city's 
Cleanup Week, July 9 to 14. Her poster design will be used on Cleanup Week 
T-shirts. 
</P>
<P>
Second place was won by Raul Gonzalo of St. Rose of Lima School, and third 
place went to Ana Medrano of Heliotrope Avenue School. 
</P>
<P>
On July 14, volunteer residents will meet at 8 a.m. at the chamber office to do 
cleanup work at various sites around the city. Volunteers will work from 8 a.m 
to noon. Afterward, there will be a barbecue at Maywood City Park, 4801 E. 58th 
St., for all those who help out. For more information, call Claire Beard at the 
Chamber of Commerce, 562-3373. 
</P>
</TEXT>
