<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENT PAPERBACKS: THE BUS OF DREAMS BY MARY MORRIS (PENGUIN: $7.95) 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A collection of competent but uninvolving stories reprinted from various 
magazines. 
</P>
<P>
Mary Morris can put words together in ways that suggest a character or set a 
mood, but these brief vignettes involving alcoholic fathers, quarreling 
families and unhappy lovers lack a distinguishing voice. The stories seem 
vaguely familiar, as if the reader had skimmed them in the dentist's waiting 
room a few weeks earlier. If such a thing as generic fiction exists, Morris has 
pioneered it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
