<P>
HOMETOWN WELCOMES EXPLORER OF ANTARCTIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ELY, Minn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Antarctic explorer Will Steger got a rousing welcome home Saturday from nearly 
all of the 4,289 residents of his hometown in the north woods. 
</P>
<P>
"Incredible," was Steger's only reaction after thousands showered him with 
confetti and good wishes during a parade through the tiny business district. 
</P>
<P>
The 45-year-old explorer left Ely last July to serve as co-leader of the 
six-member International Trans-Antarctica Expedition, the longest unmechanized 
passage across the frozen continent. 
</P>
<P>
After the parade Steger posed for pictures and signed autographs -- on paper 
and on the clothes on some people's backs. 
</P>
