FIRMS IMPLICATED IN IRAQ CANNON PLANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Leading West German firms help to build an Iraqi weapons factory where a giant 
cannon was to be made, the Hamburg-based news magazine Der Spiegel said. 
</P>
<P>
The weekly said "confiscated documents" showed that the factory near Baghdad 
was designed to produce guns. Experts feared that it was also where a cannon 
with a barrel about 150 yards long and with a range of 600 miles was to be 
built. Britain and other West European countries have confiscated shipments 
suspected of being parts for an Iraqi supergun that could hit Israel. 
