<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRIVER SHOT IN FACE AS HE ENTERS VEHICLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ORANGE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man who had just gotten into his car in his apartment garage was shot in the 
face Saturday morning, apparently by a robber who then fled. 
</P>
<P>
Police identified the victim as Miguel Ontivarez Guzman, 25, of 992 N. Highland 
St., Apt. 2. He was listed in critical condition at Western Medical 
Center-Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
Police said they suspect that it was a robbery attempt. As soon as Guzman got 
into his driver's seat about 7:10 a.m., he heard a voice behind him, turned 
toward the back seat and was shot in the face, officers said. 
</P>
<P>
Guzman staggered back to his apartment, where friends called police. 
</P>
<P>
Officers said they could not yet tell whether the gunman stole anything. 
</P>
</TEXT>
