<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM-SAN JUAN VAN POOL STARTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A new van pool that will take commuting South Orange County residents to 
workplaces in Anaheim will begin Monday morning. 
</P>
<P>
Established and subsidized by the city, the pool offers space for public 
employees and any other workers commuting from South County to jobs near the 
Anaheim Civic Center. 
</P>
<P>
The 12-seat van will leave Escondido in northern San Diego County at 5:30 a.m. 
Monday through Friday, stop once in San Juan Capistrano, then arrive in Anaheim 
at 7 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
More stops will be added as needed, city officials said. The return trip will 
leave Anaheim at 3:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
City employees will ride for $75 monthly; others will pay $90. More information 
is available and seats can be reserved at (714) 999-KARS. 
</P>
</TEXT>
