<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENTS: A GUIDE TO THE BEST OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA; 
</P>
<P>
SHOPTALK; 
</P>
<P>
BURIED TREASURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK EHRMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"A hoy there, mate! We've gathered many a treasure from foreign shores. . . ." 
Who said that? Relax, it's only the electronically wired pirate dummy stationed 
by the front door, the first clue that you've embarked on a voyage into the 
unusual. Indeed, the nautical treasures waiting to be discovered in The Sea are 
wondrous and plentiful -- much like the wonders of the sea itself. 
</P>
<P>
A circus of giant fiberglass dolphins, sharks and whales hangs from the 
ceiling. Skeletons of sea mammals adorn the walls. As you navigate your way 
through the aisles, you'll encounter shells most landlubbers never knew 
existed, scrimshaw, minerals, fossils, ships in bottles and naval relics. If 
it's related to the seven seas, you'll find it here -- somewhere. 
</P>
<P>
 The Sea, 305 N. Harbor Blvd., San Pedro; (213) 831-1694. MARK EHRMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
