<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENTS: A GUIDE TO THE BEST OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA; 
</P>
<P>
SHOPTALK; 
</P>
<P>
SCANNING THE GLOBE FOR GIFTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DIANE BAILEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHOPPERS WHO NEED a break from their neighborhood mall but are not quite ready 
for Melrose Avenue might want to try the Guildhouse. Housed in a converted 
men's dormitory next to Barlow Hospital in Elysian Park, the Guildhouse doesn't 
stock the dusty trinkets found in most hospital gift shops; retired 
doctor-and-nurse couple Arnold and Margaret Freed scour the world for 
treasures, from hand-carved wooden birds from China to hand-carved ceramics 
from Uruguay. 
</P>
<P>
"Every place I go -- all over the world -- I stick my nose in shops and see 
what they're selling," Margaret Freed says. The beautifully handmade Polish 
boxes finished by chip carving are one such recent Guildhouse addition. "The 
government put sanctions on these things years ago," she explains. Now, with 
the changes in Eastern Europe, tariffs have been lifted, and the boxes are once 
again available. "This is the first shipment we've been able to get in a long 
time." 
</P>
<P>
Gifts from the Guildhouse (open weekend afternoons only) are priced to suit 
even the tightest budgets, and proceeds benefit Barlow Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Guildhouse, 2000 Stadium Way, Los Angeles; (213) 250-3894. 
</P>
<P>
DIANE BAILEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
